<subSubSection pageId="271" pageNumber="876" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="271.[786,1380,2581,3003]" lastBlockId="271.[172,1378,3008,3474]" pageId="271" pageNumber="876">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[786,1066,2934,2963]" pageId="271" pageNumber="876">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 185— 207 mm, tail 156-185 mm, ear 17-4-19-6 mm, hindfoot 45-47 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Sulawesi Forest Rat is medium-sized and distinctive, with comparatively short and wavy pelage and short dark guard hairs. Dorsum is chestnut brown or rich reddish brown (older specimen is reddish all around), with light slate or brownish gray underfur and hair bases. Venter is ocherous, with hairs having pale gray bases. Feet are brown. Tail is only ¢.85% of head-body length, unicolored blackish brown, and sparsely furred. Skull is elongated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
